        "number": 622,
        "repo": "sonic-platform-common",
        "comment_at": "2026-02-15T11:10:56Z",
        "comment_author": "benle7",
        "comment_body": "> @benle7 the BMC root password is set in the build parameters, correct? can you please add reference to the build parameter? what happen when the build param is not set? will the functionality will exit with error information ?\r\n\r\nCorrect - BMC_ROOT_ACCOUNT_DEFAULT_PASSWORD\r\nhttps://github.com/sonic-net/sonic-buildimage/blob/1e4c149f9acb2a5a939223e8c0e82bf296817fe5/rules/config#L62\r\n\r\nIf the variable is not set, the SONiC command to reset the BMC root password will fail with an error log of\r\n\"BMC root account default password not found\"."
    },
